 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Upon seeing a Raffle for Addison's Works unfill'd.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">gentle Beaux, and thoughtless Belles,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who gaily rove at ,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With Pockets full; and empty Looks,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Raffling for ev'ry Toy — but Books:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Should  immortal Page</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">(The Glory of his Land and Age)</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Want two Subscriptions to be full,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The World will dare pronounce you dull.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">wise — subscribe — and shew, at least;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That you have one Pretence to Taste.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
